      "level": 1,
      "ordinal": 2,
      "summary": "The CII formula is basically the product of \"Full Voyage Fuel Burned and Carbon Factor (depending on fuel type used)\" divided by the product of \"Summer Deadweight Ton (DWT) and Full Distance (both ballast and laden)\". The result is to calculate the amount of CO2 (grams) emitted per DWTnautical mile aka carbon intensity.",
